  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "On the contrary, values (often those of the designers) become embedded into technologies during their design (van de Poel, 2020), resulting in e.g.",
    "safety by design (van de Poel & Robaey, 2017) and privacy by design (Gürses et al., 2011).",
    "The way in which this happens, ideally, is that after determining the relevant values for a technology under development these are further specified into norms.",
    "These more detailed specifications show what aspects of these values filter into the technology (e.g.",
    "privacy can be both about preventing harms such as identity theft and about preserving autonomy)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "safety by design (van de Poel & Robaey, 2017) and privacy by design (Gürses et al., 2011)."
  ]
}